body:
When both `multi_query` and `hybrid_search` are enabled, each query triggers up to 4 separate embedding calls (line 616) and 4 separate BM25 searches (line 630). With HyDE additionally enabled, there's also an LLM call for the hypothetical document generation. This means a single user query can result in 4 embedding calls + 4 BM25 searches + 1 HyDE LLM call + the final LLM completion — which could be quite slow with cloud providers. Consider documenting this latency tradeoff, or batching the embedding calls instead of looping one by one.
```suggestion
             # HyDE uses a single hypothetical document as the vector query
             all_vector_results.extend(
                 self.vector_store.search(
                     self.embedding.embed_query(vector_query),
                     top_k=fetch_k,
                     filter_dict=filters,
                 )
             )
        else:
             # When multi_query is enabled, batch embed all queries to avoid
             # multiple sequential embedding calls (latency/cost optimization).
             if len(search_queries) == 1:
                 sq = search_queries[0]
                 all_vector_results.extend(
                     self.vector_store.search(
                         self.embedding.embed_query(sq),
                         top_k=fetch_k,
                         filter_dict=filters,
                     )
                 )
             else:
                 embeddings = self.embedding.embed(search_queries)
                 for emb in embeddings:
                     all_vector_results.extend(
                         self.vector_store.search(
                             emb,
                             top_k=fetch_k,
                             filter_dict=filters,
                         )
                     )
